cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on learning visuomotor subroutines from egocentric video data. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper demonstrates the behavior of the learned subroutines on a real robotic platform. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper proposes a method to learn hierarchical abstractions using self-supervised inverse models and latent intent-conditioned policies. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper uses reinforcement learning and planning techniques to demonstrate the utility of the learned subroutines. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with navigation and control of a robotic platform.
